WEBVTT

1
00:00:28.143 --> 00:00:32.423 line:82%
"Sanskrit mantra"

2
00:00:33.455 --> 00:00:37.846 line:82%
"Sanskrit mantra"

3
00:00:38.601 --> 00:00:42.538 line:82%
"Sanskrit mantra"

4
00:00:43.336 --> 00:00:48.195 line:82%
"Sanskrit mantra"

5
00:00:53.724 --> 00:00:54.763 line:82%
It's so dark in here.

6
00:00:59.883 --> 00:01:00.923 line:82%
What's the matter?

7
00:01:01.764 --> 00:01:03.122 line:82%
It's so dark in here.

8
00:01:04.323 --> 00:01:05.443 line:82%
Switch on the light then.

9
00:01:06.044 --> 00:01:08.443 line:82%
- Where's the switch?
- I don't know. I'm very scared.

10
00:01:08.784 --> 00:01:09.903 line:82%
Here it is.

11
00:01:13.104 --> 00:01:14.142 line:82%
Wow.

12
00:01:19.744 --> 00:01:22.103 line:82%
This place is so cool.

13
00:01:22.444 --> 00:01:24.442 line:82%
Isn't it? Okay, tell me.

14
00:01:24.683 --> 00:01:26.803 line:82%
Would you find any place
as romantic as this in Goa?

15
00:01:27.144 --> 00:01:28.583 line:82%
No one will ever know.

16
00:01:29.003 --> 00:01:31.803 line:82%
By the way, Rohan,
whom does this house belong to?

17
00:01:40.883 --> 00:01:42.123 line:82%
It's really so interesting.

18
00:01:42.244 --> 00:01:46.402 line:82%
This big, empty house has
just me, you and a ghost.

19
00:01:52.924 --> 00:01:54.763 line:82%
Have you brought
something to eat or not?

20
00:01:54.827 --> 00:01:57.226 line:82%
Of course, I have. And you
know what I've arranged for?

21
00:01:57.443 --> 00:01:59.443 line:82%
A candlelight dinner.
That too, with champagne.

22
00:02:00.004 --> 00:02:01.761 line:82%
Perfect. Then get it ready.

23
00:02:01.845 --> 00:02:03.843 line:82%
- I'll go freshen up quickly.
- Okay. I'll come along.

24
00:02:04.883 --> 00:02:07.402 line:82%
I'll go and freshen up.
You get the dinner ready.

25
00:02:07.689 --> 00:02:09.289 line:82%
- Tina... Tina.
- Bye.

26
00:02:16.523 --> 00:02:17.563 line:82%
You're still here?

27
00:02:21.364 --> 00:02:23.643 line:82%
Please, let's go downstairs.
I'm starving.

28
00:02:23.723 --> 00:02:26.323 line:82%
Tina, dinner is ready.

29
00:02:38.723 --> 00:02:40.963 line:82%
- What? - But you were just
standing there, ain't you?

30
00:02:41.084 --> 00:02:42.922 line:82%
What? Why would I stand there?

31
00:02:43.204 --> 00:02:44.842 line:82%
I was downstairs
getting the dinner ready.

32
00:02:45.124 --> 00:02:46.402 line:82%
Come on. Let me show
you what I've made.

33
00:02:46.523 --> 00:02:47.563 line:82%
Then who was that?

34
00:02:48.364 --> 00:02:49.443 line:82%
Oh, I get it.

35
00:02:50.084 --> 00:02:52.522 line:82%
Now, you're trying to scare me.
Wait.

36
00:02:53.444 --> 00:02:55.323 line:82%
I got scared. How cute you are!

37
00:02:55.444 --> 00:02:56.722 line:82%
Come on, let me show
you what I've made.

38
00:02:56.963 --> 00:02:59.482 line:82%
I've made an excellent dinner.
And I've lit some candles, too.

39
00:02:59.564 --> 00:03:01.402 line:82%
Look. See how
beautiful it looks. Come here.

40
00:03:01.944 --> 00:03:04.143 line:82%
Hey, hey. Honey, our
candle will blow out.

41
00:03:04.224 --> 00:03:07.182 line:82%
Please, close the window.
Close the window.

42
00:03:08.912 --> 00:03:09.951 line:82%
Quickly.

43
00:03:10.263 --> 00:03:12.062 line:82%
Hold it.

44
00:03:16.665 --> 00:03:17.705 line:82%
Rohan, there's someone over there.

45
00:03:18.024 --> 00:03:19.783 line:82%
Tina, enough.
That's quite enough now.

46
00:03:19.863 --> 00:03:21.343 line:82%
I just saw someone. Please,
let's leave.

47
00:03:21.423 --> 00:03:22.583 line:82%
You're just imagining things.

48
00:03:24.464 --> 00:03:26.342 line:82%
Now why are you screaming?
It's just a power cut.

49
00:03:27.384 --> 00:03:28.423 line:82%
The TV is on.

50
00:03:28.503 --> 00:03:30.343 line:82%
Tina, there's no electricity.
How can the TV work?

51
00:03:30.423 --> 00:03:31.982 line:82%
Rohan, I'm telling you.
There's someone here.

52
00:03:32.064 --> 00:03:33.223 line:82%
- Please. Listen to me. Let's leave.
- Tina. Enough.

53
00:03:33.303 --> 00:03:35.023 line:82%
Tina, stop it. Stop it.
You're ruining the evening.

54
00:03:35.304 --> 00:03:36.703 line:82%
Stop it. Wait here.

55
00:03:38.103 --> 00:03:39.383 line:82%
Rohan, please
believe me. I'm not lying.

56
00:03:39.504 --> 00:03:41.063 line:82%
- Let's see now.
- I've seen something. Please.

57
00:03:41.144 --> 00:03:42.662 line:82%
Is anyone here?

58
00:03:42.744 --> 00:03:43.783 line:82%
- Stop it, Rohan.
- Is anyone there?

59
00:03:43.863 --> 00:03:45.062 line:82%
- There is.
- Did you see anyone?

60
00:03:45.224 --> 00:03:48.343 line:82%
Look here. Look here, too. Tina,
there's no one here.

61
00:05:58.503 --> 00:06:00.023 line:82%
Give me the keys.

62
00:06:00.744 --> 00:06:03.143 line:82%
Hey, Antony, get up.
Get out of here. Go.

63
00:06:03.224 --> 00:06:05.222 line:82%
Hey, let me stay here.
I'll take care of it.

64
00:06:05.703 --> 00:06:06.743 line:82%
You can't take care of yourself,
but you'd like...

65
00:06:06.824 --> 00:06:07.862 line:82%
to take care of this house?

66
00:06:07.944 --> 00:06:09.422 line:82%
Come on, get up. Get out of here.

67
00:06:09.543 --> 00:06:11.903 line:82%
Hey. This is my house.

68
00:06:12.744 --> 00:06:15.623 line:82%
No one apart from me
would dare to stay here.

69
00:06:16.263 --> 00:06:17.543 line:82%
A ghost lives here.

70
00:06:18.543 --> 00:06:21.623 line:82%
Hey, Jagan. Tell me,
who will stay here?

71
00:06:26.583 --> 00:06:30.542 line:82%
Come on, come on. See,
Banku. This... All this is Goa.

72
00:06:30.903 --> 00:06:33.103 line:82%
- Wow.
- Where's our house?

73
00:06:33.303 --> 00:06:35.543 line:82%
Our house... That's our house.

74
00:06:35.784 --> 00:06:37.543 line:82%
- That isn't our house.
- Hey.

75
00:06:37.623 --> 00:06:40.262 line:82%
- Stop it. Stop it. You talk rubbish.
- Hey, how would you know?

76
00:06:40.344 --> 00:06:41.702 line:82%
You were sleeping when we
came here to house-hunt.

77
00:06:41.943 --> 00:06:43.303 line:82%
- Really?
- Yes, like always.

78
00:06:43.383 --> 00:06:44.663 line:82%
- Okay. Now, let's go.
- Listen, just a minute. Listen...

79
00:06:44.864 --> 00:06:47.822 line:82%
- Let me just show him. Hey.
- Come on.

80
00:06:47.943 --> 00:06:48.983 line:82%
Okay, come on.

81
00:06:56.343 --> 00:06:58.583 line:82%
Come, come. Pick my taxi, sir.

82
00:06:58.664 --> 00:07:00.023 line:82%
- Come, come. Sir...
- Sir.

83
00:07:00.224 --> 00:07:01.543 line:82%
Let go off my suitcase at least.

84
00:07:01.623 --> 00:07:03.943 line:82%
Hey, just a moment. What are
you doing? Aditya, tell them.

85
00:07:04.023 --> 00:07:05.663 line:82%
We don't want to go sightseeing.
Wait. Tell them.

86
00:07:05.984 --> 00:07:07.622 line:82%
Tell them the name of the road.
Tell them the address quickly.

87
00:07:07.704 --> 00:07:09.223 line:82%
- Don't... Don't you remember?
Wait a minute. - Hey, stop.

88
00:07:09.303 --> 00:07:11.743 line:82%
- Nath Villa.
- Nath... You can take them.

89
00:07:11.823 --> 00:07:14.303 line:82%
- What happened? Hey, brother... brother...
- What happened?

90
00:07:14.583 --> 00:07:17.063 line:82%
- What happened?
- They were just fighting to take us.

91
00:07:17.144 --> 00:07:18.182 line:82%
What's the matter now?

92
00:07:18.423 --> 00:07:20.942 line:82%
Madam, no one is
going to take you there.

93
00:07:21.303 --> 00:07:24.143 line:82%
- Sir, no one will take you there.
- Why?

94
00:07:24.663 --> 00:07:26.783 line:82%
I'd advise you not to go there either.

95
00:07:26.904 --> 00:07:29.023 line:82%
Don't go if you don't want to.
We'll hire another taxi. Come, Banku.

96
00:07:29.103 --> 00:07:31.223 line:82%
Listen, sir. I'll take you
there if you want. Come.

97
00:07:31.704 --> 00:07:33.662 line:82%
- Take that.
- Come.

98
00:07:33.783 --> 00:07:34.823 line:82%
And hold this.

99
00:07:35.144 --> 00:07:36.263 line:82%
Come, kid.

100
00:07:40.424 --> 00:07:43.223 line:82%
"Chin... Chinchpokli."

101
00:07:43.304 --> 00:07:45.623 line:82%
"The bus stops when the
conductor rings the bell."

102
00:07:45.704 --> 00:07:46.742 line:82%
You sing well.

103
00:07:47.264 --> 00:07:49.703 line:82%
By the way, why didn't the other
taxis want to go to Nath Villa?

104
00:07:50.064 --> 00:07:52.262 line:82%
Sir, may I ask you
something if you don't mind?

105
00:07:52.383 --> 00:07:54.062 line:82%
Are you related to Mr. Nath?

106
00:07:54.504 --> 00:07:56.102 line:82%
No, No, we rented that house.

107
00:07:56.343 --> 00:07:57.623 line:82%
Then rent another house instead.

108
00:07:57.704 --> 00:07:59.222 line:82%
Why are you asking for trouble, sir?

109
00:07:59.384 --> 00:08:01.502 line:82%
Why? What's wrong with that place?

110
00:08:01.623 --> 00:08:04.742 line:82%
Ma'am, it's said that
there's an angry spirit there.

111
00:08:04.863 --> 00:08:07.103 line:82%
There's a ghost there. Ghost.

112
00:08:10.664 --> 00:08:12.983 line:82%
Hey, there are no such
things as ghosts. Nonsense.

113
00:08:19.104 --> 00:08:21.902 line:82%
- Hey. - Just a mention of the
ghost and the car...

114
00:08:23.304 --> 00:08:24.782 line:82%
- What happened?
- Just a moment.

115
00:08:26.823 --> 00:08:28.343 line:82%
I think the car won't
go any further, sir.

116
00:08:28.904 --> 00:08:30.463 line:82%
So? Will we have to walk?

117
00:08:30.584 --> 00:08:33.302 line:82%
- Yes, you'll have to walk from here.
- No.

118
00:08:33.384 --> 00:08:34.823 line:82%
It's very close. Come,
Banku. Let's carry your mommy...

119
00:08:34.904 --> 00:08:36.542 line:82%
- and take her along.
- Oh, no.

120
00:08:37.944 --> 00:08:40.142 line:82%
Here's Nath Villa.

121
00:08:41.624 --> 00:08:43.022 line:82%
You're Mr. Aditya, right?

122
00:08:43.543 --> 00:08:45.023 line:82%
I'm Jagan. I'm the caretaker here.

123
00:08:45.103 --> 00:08:48.303 line:82%
Take this. Take it.
Good. Here's the suitcase.

124
00:08:48.363 --> 00:08:49.523 line:82%
- Hello.
- Hello.

125
00:08:49.604 --> 00:08:51.242 line:82%
Come.

126
00:08:51.723 --> 00:08:53.882 line:82%
- Come.
- Hey. Get down, you monkey.

127
00:08:54.023 --> 00:08:55.063 line:82%
- Come on.
- Come on, Banku.

128
00:08:55.544 --> 00:08:56.583 line:82%
Come.

129
00:08:59.704 --> 00:09:02.563 line:82%
Such a big house. This is even
bigger than grandpa's house.

130
00:09:02.725 --> 00:09:05.964 line:82%
- Isn't it? - Come, I'll show you the
inside of the house. Come.

131
00:09:24.624 --> 00:09:25.662 line:82%
It's jammed.

132
00:09:25.864 --> 00:09:27.623 line:82%
How long has it been locked?

133
00:09:28.384 --> 00:09:30.623 line:82%
Not for long. I just got it cleaned.

134
00:09:30.666 --> 00:09:31.905 line:82%
As soon as I learned
you would be arriving...

135
00:09:31.944 --> 00:09:32.982 line:82%
I got it cleaned. First-class.

136
00:09:33.935 --> 00:09:36.733 line:82%
This is well-cleaned?

137
00:09:37.037 --> 00:09:41.397 line:82%
It's clean. Anyway, you'll handle
the rest of the cleanup. Right?

138
00:09:49.964 --> 00:09:52.642 line:82%
I think we'll have to
break the glass. Hey.

139
00:09:54.524 --> 00:09:56.242 line:82%
Banku, what are you doing?

140
00:09:56.723 --> 00:09:57.763 line:82%
Just what he said.

141
00:09:58.684 --> 00:09:59.722 line:82%
But...

142
00:10:00.164 --> 00:10:01.923 line:82%
No problem.
We'll install another one.

143
00:10:02.003 --> 00:10:03.922 line:82%
- So I'll break it completely then.
- Good idea.

144
00:10:08.723 --> 00:10:10.363 line:82%
Hey, I was just...

145
00:10:10.584 --> 00:10:12.583 line:82%
I wonder how I'll
handle all this by myself.

146
00:10:12.903 --> 00:10:15.383 line:82%
Hey, now that it's broken, open
the window and then open the door.

147
00:10:17.223 --> 00:10:20.263 line:82%
- Come. I'll get it.
- Yes, get the luggage.

148
00:10:20.504 --> 00:10:21.743 line:82%
Such a big house.

149
00:10:22.263 --> 00:10:25.142 line:82%
- Oh, my God. Such a big house.
- Great.

150
00:10:25.623 --> 00:10:27.863 line:82%
People used to build such
lavish houses in the old times.

151
00:10:28.263 --> 00:10:29.503 line:82%
Your company is just too much.

152
00:10:29.784 --> 00:10:32.423 line:82%
- Couldn't they find us a medium
sized house? - Anjali. Now...

153
00:10:32.504 --> 00:10:34.663 line:82%
Ma'am, there's also a terrace upstairs.

154
00:10:34.743 --> 00:10:35.783 line:82%
- Oh, wow. There's a terrace, too.
- What?

155
00:10:35.864 --> 00:10:37.262 line:82%
- Yes.
- No... Banku.

156
00:10:37.344 --> 00:10:39.302 line:82%
Those are the stairs,
Banku. You'll fall down...

157
00:10:41.024 --> 00:10:43.463 line:82%
Okay. Ma'am, you'll get
water 24 hours a day here.

158
00:10:43.544 --> 00:10:45.823 line:82%
You can wash clothes and
utensils whenever you want.

159
00:10:45.944 --> 00:10:48.023 line:82%
Hey, she needs just an hour
for the clothes and utensils.

160
00:10:48.104 --> 00:10:49.262 line:82%
Anjali does everything very fast.

161
00:10:49.383 --> 00:10:51.662 line:82%
- Yes. So come. I'll show you the kitchen.
- You're too much, Aditya.

162
00:10:51.744 --> 00:10:54.263 line:82%
- Go see the kitchen. Go on.
- Come.

163
00:10:55.544 --> 00:10:56.903 line:82%
- This one, right?
- Right ahead. Yes.

164
00:10:59.984 --> 00:11:01.022 line:82%
Here, sir.

165
00:11:01.743 --> 00:11:04.382 line:82%
Listen, I wanted to ask you something.

166
00:11:06.504 --> 00:11:09.062 line:82%
There are a lot of rumors
going around about this house.

167
00:11:09.384 --> 00:11:14.783 line:82%
Even the cabbie was saying
that there are ghosts here.

168
00:11:14.904 --> 00:11:16.543 line:82%
That's all nonsense, sir.

169
00:11:17.103 --> 00:11:20.543 line:82%
Look, actually, the owner of
this house stays in the US.

170
00:11:20.664 --> 00:11:23.102 line:82%
I have the responsibility of
this house, so they're jealous.

171
00:11:23.223 --> 00:11:24.662 line:82%
They just spread false stories.

172
00:11:25.184 --> 00:11:28.262 line:82%
Trust me, sir. It's
nothing like that. Sign here.

173
00:11:28.424 --> 00:11:29.462 line:82%
Mama.

174
00:11:31.263 --> 00:11:33.383 line:82%
- Banku.
- Mama.

175
00:11:33.543 --> 00:11:35.623 line:82%
- What happened? Banku.
- Calm down, Anjali.

176
00:11:36.984 --> 00:11:38.942 line:82%
- Mama.
- Banku.

177
00:11:39.464 --> 00:11:40.502 line:82%
- What happened, Banku?
- What happened?

178
00:11:40.623 --> 00:11:41.863 line:82%
It's such a huge terrace.

179
00:11:41.943 --> 00:11:44.303 line:82%
It'll be so much fun
to play cricket here.

180
00:11:44.424 --> 00:11:47.783 line:82%
- So why were you screaming for that?
- Look how scared your mama got.

181
00:11:47.943 --> 00:11:50.983 line:82%
- I... I wasn't scared, but...
- But I got scared.

182
00:11:52.664 --> 00:11:54.943 line:82%
- You have a very naughty kid.
- He's too much.

183
00:11:55.064 --> 00:11:58.423 line:82%
- Come, let's go downstairs, Son.
- Come on, bowl to me.

184
00:11:59.223 --> 00:12:01.943 line:82%
- Come on.
- Let's go downstairs now.

185
00:12:02.064 --> 00:12:03.990 line:82%
Kids are bound to be mischievous,
Mr. Jagan.

186
00:12:04.177 --> 00:12:06.038 line:82%
By the way, how many kids
do you have?

187
00:12:06.464 --> 00:12:08.582 line:82%
I have two daughters.
They are very tranquil.

188
00:12:09.344 --> 00:12:10.823 line:82%
It's for them that
I have to work hard outside...

189
00:12:10.904 --> 00:12:12.383 line:82%
- the house all day.
- Banku.

190
00:12:12.504 --> 00:12:14.582 line:82%
Yes, one has to stay out
of the house for work.

191
00:12:14.671 --> 00:12:16.110 line:82%
Look at me, I stay out for months.

192
00:12:16.481 --> 00:12:17.521 line:82%
Months? What do you mean?

193
00:12:17.764 --> 00:12:19.282 line:82%
I'm the chief
engineer on a cruise ship.

194
00:12:19.364 --> 00:12:22.363 line:82%
- I have to go where the cruise goes.
- Okay.

195
00:12:22.444 --> 00:12:24.163 line:82%
And he leaves us behind.

196
00:12:24.644 --> 00:12:28.123 line:82%
That's why I wanted a house where
I don't have to worry about them.

197
00:12:28.204 --> 00:12:29.242 line:82%
Where they are safe.

198
00:12:30.323 --> 00:12:31.762 line:82%
Yes, it's very safe here.

199
00:12:31.844 --> 00:12:34.653 line:82%
You don't have to worry
about anything here, but just...

200
00:12:34.741 --> 00:12:35.980 line:82%
Oh, yes. I forgot about this.

201
00:12:41.191 --> 00:12:43.991 line:82%
What? So what else
could have I made?

202
00:12:44.243 --> 00:12:46.443 line:82%
Nothing. Sandwiches
are our favorite.

203
00:12:46.643 --> 00:12:48.163 line:82%
That's why it's
sandwiches for breakfast...

204
00:12:48.244 --> 00:12:51.283 line:82%
sandwiches for lunch,
sandwiches for dinner.

205
00:12:51.364 --> 00:12:52.642 line:82%
Sandwich, sandwich. Witch.

206
00:12:53.204 --> 00:12:54.243 line:82%
Adi.

207
00:12:54.884 --> 00:12:55.923 line:82%
- Papa...
- Yes?

208
00:12:56.003 --> 00:12:58.162 line:82%
Will mommy give me
sandwiches in the lunchbox, too?

209
00:12:58.283 --> 00:12:59.763 line:82%
No, no. She'll make
instant noodles sometimes.

210
00:13:00.215 --> 00:13:02.044 line:82%
- I can hear everything.
- Good then.

211
00:13:03.744 --> 00:13:05.382 line:82%
Okay, when is your cruise leaving?

212
00:13:06.164 --> 00:13:07.203 line:82%
Two days from now.

213
00:13:07.510 --> 00:13:08.549 line:82%
No. Not at all.

214
00:13:08.941 --> 00:13:11.253 line:82%
You can't go anywhere till
